  "market_context": "Daily chart of NQ1! showing a bearish C2 closure near 25,200–25,400 zone (labeled 'C2'), with subsequent price action on lower time frames (15-min and 1-min) revealing no lower-timeframe change in state of delivery before price swept the high.",
  "key_observation": "A candle-2 closure occurred (price took out prior high and closed back below), but lower-timeframe analysis showed no closure through the series of candles forming that high—i.e., no CISD—so the swing point was not confirmed.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified a bearish C2 closure on the daily chart where price took out the previous high and closed back below it.",
    "Step 2: Analyst checked the lower time frame (15-min/1-min) to verify if a change in state of delivery (CISD) had occurred—specifically, whether price closed below the series of candles that formed the high.",
    "Step 3: Analyst observed that no CISD had yet formed; the series of candles remained unbroken on the lower timeframe.",
    "Step 4: Analyst noted that because CISD was absent, the C2 closure was invalid as a reversal signal, and price subsequently swept the high, avoiding a losing short trade."
  ],
  "outcome": "No trade taken; losses prevented by waiting for CISD confirmation",
  "lessons": "A C2 closure alone is insufficient for a valid reversal setup; it must be paired with lower-timeframe CISD (closure through the opposing candle series) to confirm the swing point and avoid false signals.",
